# Git Commit Rules

## Commit Discipline
- Every small feature block (e.g., migrating an API, modifying a directory) must be immediately `git add` and `git commit`
- Never combine thousands of lines of code into a single commit
- Commit message format: `type(scope): description`
- type options: feat/fix/refactor/build/chore/docs/test
- All git commit messages MUST be written strictly in English, following the Conventional Commits standard. NEVER use Chinese in commit messages.
